text.tspan: Dear Jesus, save me this day
Let me say, “You now live in me”
And “It’s no longer I who live;”
But dear Jesus, grace me today.
Let me live You out, Lord;
Let me magnify You through me.
I’ll let You; Lord, be my replacement.
Lord, thank You for Your mercy;
Your grace, it’s true, sustains me.
Lord, I realize I’m weak and faint.
I need You, Jesus; speak today;
Come and infuse me more each day.
Lord I realize, I’m full of taint.
Let Your glory shine upon me.
I’m open; Lord, make me Your treasure.
Now my daily life, I’ve seen;
It’s devoid of Your dear life, Lord.
I need You, Lord. Oh! Jesus, do fill it.
Yes, fill it—still I’m short of this—
Mature, and one with You eternally.
